    "extracted_information": "Overall Review Summary:\n- TrustScore: 2.6 out of 5 (Poor) based on 998 reviews.\n- Most reviewers were unhappy, expressing concerns about delivery service, refund issues, and customer contact.\n- Opinions on product quality are mixed.\n\nOperations Feedback:\n- Significant delays in delivery and lack of order status updates are recurring issues. Many orders remain in 'pre-shipment' for extended periods (e.g., 3-8+ days without movement after label creation).\n- Company perceived to lack concern regarding shipping delays.\n- Instances of false shipping information being sent (e.g., tracking numbers indicating mailing date earlier than actual warehouse departure).\n- Orders being charged before actual shipment.\n- Difficulty processing orders.\n- Issue with international shipping: The website allows international orders despite the company currently not shipping internationally, leading to cancellations and delays in reimbursement.\n- Non-refundable policy for opened products.\n- One positive instance noted where replacement products were sent when an order didn't show up.\n\nProduct Quality Feedback:\n- Mixed opinions on product quality, with no clear consensus.\n- Negative experiences include:\n    - \"Strongest gummy ever\" advertised as ineffective, containing mostly CBD and being non-psychoactive.\n    - Gummies generally considered a \"WASTE OF MONEY!\" and ineffective.\n    - Vapes/carts are often described as \"terrible,\" clogging, leaking, or appearing of low/bad quality.\n    - Moonrocks reported as melted, liquid blobs.\n    - Products not working or being ineffective (e.g., \"feel nothing\" from vapes).\n    - Misrepresentation of product composition: Vapes advertised with specific cannabinoids (e.g., THCA, THCP) found to be predominantly Delta 8 THC based on lab results, with little to no advertised cannabinoids.\n    - Some products tasting like Delta 8 even when labs don't indicate it.\n- Positive experiences include:\n    - Some users find Binoid's products strong and effective, even compared to medical dispensaries.\n\nCustomer Service Feedback:\n- Significant frustration with lack of responsiveness and assistance.\n- Many reports of no response to emails, calls, or general unresponsiveness.\n- Difficulties getting assistance or clarification on issues.\n- Negative experiences with refunds: Claims of not receiving refunds for canceled orders or unsatisfactory products.\n- Issues with account management: Accounts being disabled multiple times without explanation, and refusal to respond to inquiries about re-opening accounts.\n- Some experiences of "gaslighting" when complaining about issues (e.g., being blamed for issues with product misrepresentation or review posting).\n- One positive experience noted where a customer service representative (Giua) was professional, prompt, polite, showed concern, and resolved issues, advising on return policy.\n\nWebsite-Related Feedback:\n- Company is accused of only posting positive/fake reviews and suppressing negative ones, even after identity verification and attempts from different accounts.\n- Website's address system allows international orders despite no international shipping (false advertising).\n- Users note that the website's fancy packaging and interface can be deceiving.\n- Company advertises 2-4 day shipping which reviewers state is untrue.\n- Binoid's own website is expected by users not to post their negative reviews.",
